line_1: He thought the Park in Drury-lane,
Nine years! cries he, who high in Drury-lane
line_2: Lull'd by soft Zephyrs thro' the broken Pane,

line_1: My father was a play'r in Drury-lane,
line_2: To shew that my pretensions are not vain,

line_1: Supply'd by Goodman's fields and Drury-lane.
line_2: With ease that loss the nation might sustain,
And o'er the two great empires still I reign
